If you want a much simpler approach, you can save the request on the connect handler so that you have it on any subsequent events. And this technique works on namespaces or function based events alike.

```python
requests = {}

@socketio.on('connect')
def on_connect(sid, environ):
    requests[sid] = environ['aiohttp.request']

@socketio.on('message')
def on_message(sid, data):
    print('request:', requests[sid])

@socketio.on('disconnect')
def on_disconnect(sid):
    del requests[sid]
```

