@TheoJL Sorry to hear you're having this problem. It seems that this is a result of the path that the Ubuntu package took to get to it's current renewal configuration. For a while it was set up as systemd timers, which ran from those directories. Unfortunately this was set up in such a way that it'd override pre-existing cron renewal configurations, so it was changed back to a cronjob. It seems like now it also tries to include those systemd folders. But as you've noticed - if you skip over that version of the package you never get those folders and then get an error on renewal.
Hopefully @oerdnj is aware of this problem and has some thoughts on how to fix it for users who don't have the `pre-hook.d` and `post-hook.d` folders.
To fix your problem in the short term, I'd edit your `www.testsite.se.conf` file to remove references to these folders. Or make blank folders that correspond to the ones being referenced.

